<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12967.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your August 23, 9 p.m. The President will be pleased to render any
                            assistance in his power in securing a conference between the First Chief
                            Carranza and Zapata. You may say that this Government is ready to do all
                            it can in every legitimate way to advance the welfare of the people of
                            Mexico and will be pleased to have the First Chief consult freely and
                            fully about any matter in which he thinks assistance can be
                            rendered.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>